________________________________________________________________________

*1. Stimulus Payments Update* ________________________________________________________________________

Look for updates on the IRS.gov stimulus payments [ http://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=177937,00.html ] page, also available in Spanish [ http://www.irs.gov/espanol/article/0,,id=180561,00.html ]. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*2. Recent Disaster Relief* ________________________________________________________________________

Victims of Tropical Storm Fay in Florida [ http://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=186300,00.html ] may qualify for IRS disaster relief. The IRS is also monitoring damage from Hurricane Gustav. Be sure to check for updates on the tax relief in disaster situations [ http://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=108362,00.html ] page. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*3. Tax Talk Today Reminder* ________________________________________________________________________

See the Sept. 9 Tax Talk Today [ http://www.taxtalktoday.com/ ] on EITC due diligence. Tune in before 2:00 p.m. ET to get any program materials available. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*4. September Phone Forum for Practitioners* ________________________________________________________________________

Check out the upcoming free phone forum [ http://www.irs.gov/businesses/small/article/0,,id=158856,00.html#3 ] on Sept. 17. Find out about the field audit process and working toward a mutual commitment date. Sign up now and be sure to use the correct conference access code when registering. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*5. Last Nationwide Tax Forum* ________________________________________________________________________

Sign up now for the last tax forum [ http://www.taxforuminfo.com/ ] of the season in San Diego Sept. 9-11. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*6. Department of Justice (DOJ) Tax Cases* ________________________________________________________________________

Read about the latest injunctions against tax return preparers and tax fraud promoters at the DOJ [ http://www.usdoj.gov/tax/taxpress2008.htm ] Web site. 

Back to top [ #top ] 

________________________________________________________________________

*7. Technical Guidance* ________________________________________________________________________

Announcement 2008-84 [ http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/a-08-84.pdf ] makes necessary modifications to the transition rules of Rev. Proc. 2008-52, which updates the procedures by which taxpayers may obtain automatic consent to change certain methods of accounting. It will be published in IRB 2008-38 dated Sept. 22, 2008. 

Revenue Procedure 2008-54 [ http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rp-08-54.pdf ] provides guidance on the increased amount of section 179 expensing provided by the Economic Stimulus Act of 2008 (Act), and how the new rules interact with the increased amount of section 179 expensing for the GO Zone and the Kansas disaster area. It will be published in IRB 2008-38 dated Sept. 22, 2008. 

Revenue Ruling 2008-47 [ http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rr-08-47.pdf ] provides the rates for interest on tax overpayment and underpayments for the calendar quarter beginning Oct. 1, 2008. It will be published in IRB 2008-39 dated Sept. 29, 2008. 
 

Back to top [ #top ] 

