      <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><a href="#top">Back to top</a> 
      </p> 
      <hr /> <a name="seventh"></a><b>7. Technical Guidance</b> 
      <hr /> 
      <p><a title="" href="http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/a-08-84.pdf" target="">Announcement 2008-84</a> makes necessary modifications to the transition rules of Rev. Proc. 2008-52, which updates the procedures by which taxpayers may obtain automatic consent to change certain methods of accounting. It will be published in IRB 2008-38 dated Sept. 22, 2008.
        <br />
        <br /><a title="" href="http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rp-08-54.pdf" target="">Revenue Procedure 2008-54</a> provides guidance on the increased amount of section 179 expensing provided by the Economic Stimulus Act of 2008 (Act), and how the new rules interact with the increased amount of section 179 expensing for the GO Zone and the Kansas disaster area. It will be published in IRB 2008-38 dated Sept. 22, 2008.
        <br />
        <br /><a title="" href="http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rr-08-47.pdf" target="">Revenue Ruling 2008-47</a> provides the rates for interest on tax overpayment and underpayments for the calendar quarter beginning Oct. 1, 2008. It will be published in IRB 2008-39 dated Sept. 29, 2008.
